Brothers Jeff and Joey Stallings, both in their 20s, fell seriously ill earlier this month after taking a 'bad batch' of synthetic marijuana in their hometown of McComb, Mississippi .
They were placed in medically-induced comas after suffering hallucinations, vomiting, night sweats and violent shaking .
Their mother Karen Stallings has appealed to others not to smoke the drug, which has been sprayed with a chemical to produce a similar sensation to marijuana .